looeee","type":"User","id":5307958,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Thanks Looeee, \r\n\r\nThat's given us enough of a steer to get the animations exporting properly.\r\n\r\nWhen exporting anims from Maya to fbx for three.js:\r\n\r\nFrame 0 has to be the bind pose.  This must be keyed and maya must be on that frame when you export.  It does not need to be included in a clip.\r\nDo not let the exporter bake animation.  \r\nAll anim must be created at 30fps\r\nClips do not need padding or extra frames, if they do not look correct an export setting is wrong.\r\nBelow are the settings from Maya 2017 U4\r\n\r\n![maya-fbx-settings-2](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/1826895\/31382917-213832cc-adb1-11e7-915f-34676300bc50.png)\r\n![maya-fbx-settings-1](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/1826895\/31382918-21546bfe-adb1-11e7-954e-d721d84c1d3b.png)\r\n\r\nHopefully this helps anyone else that stumbles across this.\r\n","created_at":"2017-10-10T10:51:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12369#issuecomment-335435202","id":335435202,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12369","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzNTQzNTIwMg==","updated_at":"2017-10-10T10:51:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/335435202","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/CorinWilkins\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/CorinWilkins\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1826895?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/CorinWilkins","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/CorinWilkins\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/CorinWilkins","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/CorinWilkins\/subscr